cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the problem of textual-visual matching, which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel loss function and a co-attention mechanism, which are related to machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper uses three datasets with identity-level annotations, which suggests that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
